					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar lying between this village and Anantamaḍugu.</p>						

						<p>Rājagaṇḍagōpāḷadēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1220, Mēśha 22, Vaiśākha śu 3, Saturday, Rōhiṇi.</hi> Irregular.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land to the god Śrīraṅganātha by the king. Further, it refers to the construction of a <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> in the garden of Soṁi-reḍḍi located near Nallaricheruvu in Pāluru in <hi rend="italic">Pālūru-nāḍu</hi> in <hi rend="italic">Pāka-nāḍu</hi> by Rājagaṇḍa-gōpaḷa and gifts to the god Mallināthadevara by Siddhayadēva-mahārāja, son of Ballirāja of Solar race.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
